Entries.default: "Welcome to the Treasure Trove, sailor." A strapping godlike blinks between the swollen, crusty tumors lining her eyes. Her lips crack, weeping a sappy substance as she speaks.
"Always, it's a pleasure to meet another of our kind." She extends a black-scaled hand to shake yours.
"So our charted routes were destined to cross again, aye?"
"Anything in my trove catches your eye, you let me know. All right?"
"Show me what you have for sale."
"You got the look of a true pirate about you. Cutthroat. Cunning. Sunburnt. I like it."
"Got a bit of a wayward wind feel about you. I'll be keeping an eye on you, I will."
"Cause trouble in my shop, and it'll be the last thing you do. Mark my words, squab." She spits into a brass pot on the floor before forcing a half-friendly smile.
